re\"\n      },\n      \"mechanism\": \"Weakly biased alanine populations undergo non-specific selection, enrichment, or partitioning to yield an L-enriched alanine pool.\",\n      \"reasoning\": \"This step is explicitly speculative and included only because the target requested is L-alanine while the validated evidence base supports mostly racemic or unspecified alanine and no robust route to enantiopure L-alanine. It operationalizes the open question acknowledged in the report rather than claiming established chemistry (de Marcellus et al., 2007; Sharma, 2022; 2015 OLEB alanine CPL study; validated report gap statement).\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"rxn_014\",\n      \"name\": \"Alanine oligomerization to alanine oligopeptides\",\n      \"inputs\": [\n        \"mol_015\"\n      ],\n      \"outputs\": [\n        \"mol_017\"\n      ],\n      \"environment\": \"Biochemical\",\n      \"agents\": [\n        \"null\"\n      ],\n      \"conditions\": {\n        \"temperature\": \"hydrothermal microflow / warm to hot aqueous conditions\",\n        \"pressure\": \"flow-reactor / hydrothermal\",\n        \"catalyst\": \"various minerals can enhance or inhibit elongation\",\n        \"aqueous\": \"true\",\n        \"other\": \"downstream assembly edge; not a route to alanine itself\"\n      },\n      \"mechanism\": \"Alanine monomers condense under hydrothermal-flow or mineral-influenced conditions to form short oligopeptides.\",\n      \"reasoning\": \"The validated report includes this as a downstream assembly edge demonstrating that once alanine exists, further prebiotic assembly is possible. It is included to satisfy the Hydrothermal \u2194 Surface \u2192 Biochemical interconnection and to keep alanine as an outgoing hub (Kawamura et al., 2005; Kawamura et al., 2018).\"\n    }\n  ],\n  \"pathways\": [\n    {\n      \"pathway_id\": \"P1\",\n      \"name\": \"Canonical Strecker full sequence\",\n      \"description\": \"Acetaldehyde, ammonia, and water form the imine/