nce >= 0.9\n\nOutput your evaluation as JSON matching the NetworkEvaluation schema.\n", "user_message": "Evaluate this synthesis network:\n\nTARGET MOLECULE: L-Alanine\nOVERALL STRATEGY: This network follows the validated literature by centering direct alanine-forming routes on (i) the classical Strecker sequence from acetaldehyde, ammonia, cyanide, and water; (ii) spark-discharge production of alanine from reduced gases; (iii) hydrothermal pyruvate amination on mixed-valence iron oxyhydroxide under alkaline redox gradients; (iv) hydrothermal simple-carbon precursor synthesis; and (v) UV/VUV astrochemical ice photochemistry. Cyanosulfidic and iron-sulfur branches are included only as literature-retained precursor-generating or inferred/contested routes. Because the evidence base does not establish direct prebiotic synthesis of enantiopure L-alanine, the target is represented as arising from racemic/unspecified alanine through a speculative low-selectivity enrichment/selection step in biochemical compartments, explicitly marked as unresolved. Ten distinct pathways are enumerated to the target, but only the Strecker, spark-discharge, hydrothermal pyruvate-amination, hydrothermal simple-carbon, and astrochemical alanine-forming branches are direct literature-supported alanine sources; the remainder are network-completion or inferred branches identified as such.\n\nMOLECULES (18 nodes):\n  - mol_001: CH4 (methane) [starting]\n  - mol_002: NH3 (ammonia) [starting]\n  - mol_003: H2 (hydrogen) [starting]\n  - mol_004: H2O (water) [starting]\n  - mol_005: H2S (hydrogen sulfide) [starting]\n  - mol_006: HCN (hydrogen cyanide) [hub_intermediate]\n  - mol_007: C2H4O (acetaldehyde) [hub_intermediate]\n  - mol_008: C2H5NO (acetaldehyde-ammonia imine/carbinolamine manifold) [intermediate]\n  - mol_009: C3H6N2 (alanine aminonitrile) [hub_intermediate]\n  - mol_010: C3H7NO (alanine amide) [intermediate]\n  - mol_011: C3H4O3 (pyruvic acid) [hub_intermediate]\n  - mol_012: FeO(OH) (i