ple carbon precursors plus ammonia yields alanine among products and is represented as also accessing the pyruvate hub; this is less mechanistically resolved than the Barge route.\",\n      \"reaction_sequence\": [\"rxn_008\", \"rxn_014\"],\n      \"key_intermediates\": [\"mol_008\", \"mol_016\"]\n    },\n    {\n      \"pathway_id\": \"P7\",\n      \"name\": \"Cyanosulfidic precursor generation feeding hydrothermal alanine synthesis\",\n      \"description\": \"HCN- and sulfide-based UV photoredox chemistry accesses the pyruvate hub, which then undergoes hydrothermal amination on mixed-valence iron oxyhydroxide to alanine; L-selection remains speculative.\",\n      \"reaction_sequence\": [\"rxn_009\", \"rxn_007\", \"rxn_014\"],\n      \"key_intermediates\": [\"mol_013\", \"mol_008\", \"mol_016\"]\n    },\n    {\n      \"pathway_id\": \"P8\",\n      \"name\": \"Cyanosulfidic precursor generation feeding iron-sulfur alanine hypothesis\",\n      \"description\": \"Surface cyanosulfidic chemistry feeds pyruvate, which is then converted to alanine in a contested sulfide-mineral hydrothermal route before speculative L-enrichment.\",\n      \"reaction_sequence\": [\"rxn_009\", \"rxn_010\", \"rxn_014\"],\n      \"key_intermediates\": [\"mol_008\", \"mol_016\"]\n    },\n    {\n      \"pathway_id\": \"P9\",\n      \"name\": \"Astrochemical UV/VUV ice route to racemic alanine\",\n      \"description\": \"Interstellar/cometary ice photochemistry yields alanine in organic residue after hydrolysis; this likely contributes racemic alanine to early Earth inventories, requiring an unresolved later L-selection step.\",\n      \"reaction_sequence\": [\"rxn_011\", \"rxn_014\"],\n      \"key_intermediates\": [\"mol_016\"]\n    },\n    {\n      \"pathway_id\": \"P10\",\n      \"name\": \"CPL-associated weak asymmetric ice route\",\n      \"description\": \"Circularly polarized UV irradiation of ice analogues yields alanine with only a very small L-excess; this is the only literature-grou