", "reasoning": "The validated corpus preserves only weak asymmetry evidence, with alanine formed after CPL irradiation but with at most very small ee values around ~1%. Both alanine and L-alanine are output here to reflect that the dominant product remains essentially alanine/racemate while a minor L-enriched fraction is possible. This should not be interpreted as a demonstrated route to enantiopure L-alanine. Mineral agents are schema-required only. Supported by de Marcellus et al. 2007; Sharma 2022; 2015 OLEB alanine CPL study."}, {"id": "rxn_013", "name": "Biochemical/prebiotic assembly of alanine into oligopeptides", "inputs": ["mol_016"], "outputs": ["mol_018"], "environment": "Biochemical", "agents": [], "conditions": {"temperature": "hydrothermal microflow / warm to hot aqueous conditions", "pressure": "flow-reactor / hydrothermal", "catalyst": "various minerals can enhance or inhibit elongation", "aqueous": "true", "other": "downstream assembly edge once alanine is available"}, "mechanism": "Alanine monomers undergo condensation/oligomerization under hydrothermal-flow or mineral-influenced conditions.", "reasoning": "This reaction is included because the validated corpus explicitly preserves alanine-to-oligopeptide assembly as downstream chemistry relevant to prebiotic progression once alanine is present. It is not a route to alanine itself. Supported by Kawamura et al. 2005; Kawamura et al. 2018."}, {"id": "rxn_014", "name": "Speculative prebiotic enrichment/selection from alanine to L-alanine", "inputs": ["mol_016"], "outputs": ["mol_017"], "environment": "Biochemical", "agents": [], "conditions": {"temperature": "variable conditions", "pressure": "ambient to localized compartmental", "catalyst": "none established", "aqueous": "true", "other": "geochemical or physical selection/enrichment step not directly validated in mounted literature"}, "mechanism": "Weak asymmetric enrichment or selective retention of one enantiomer from a predominantly racemic alanine pool.", "reasoning": "This step is explicitly speculative and included only because the requested target is L-alanine while the validated literature overwhelmingly supports racemic or unspecified alanine and no robust route to enantiopure L-alanine. The only preserved asymmetry evidence is very small CPL-associated ee, far from a demonstrated L-alanine synthesis pathway. This reaction therefore represents an unresolved gap rather than a validated synthesis. Grounded by the gap analysis in de Marcellus et al. 2007; Sharma 2022; 2015 OLEB alanine CPL study, and the executive conclusion of the supplied report."}], "pathways": [{"pathway_id": "P1", "name": "Canonical Strecker route to alanine then speculative L-selection", "description": "Best-supported mechanistic pathway: acetaldehyde forms an imine/carbinolamine manifold with ammonia and water, cyanide addition gives alanine aminonitrile, and hydrolysis via alanine amide yields alanine; L-alanine remains unresolved and requires a speculative enrichment step.", "reaction_sequence": ["rxn_001", "rxn_002", "rxn_003", "rxn_004", "rxn_014"], "key_intermediates": ["mol_005", "mol_006", "mol_007", "mol_016"]}, {"pathway_id": "P2", "name": "Partial Strecker closure from aminonitrile reservoir", "description": "A convergent route beginning from alanine aminonitrile pools generated elsewhere, followed by hydrolysis through alanine amide to alanine and then speculative L-selection.", "reaction_sequence": ["rxn_003", "rxn_004", "rxn_014"], "key_intermediates": ["mol_006", "mol_007", "mol_016"]}, {"pathway_id": "P3", "name": "Classic spark-discharge direct alanine route", "description": "Electric discharge in a reduced methane-ammonia-hydrogen-water atmosphere yields alanine directly and also populates connected Strecker feedstocks in the network; L-alanine remains unresolved.", "reaction_sequence": ["rxn_005", "rxn_014"], "key_intermediates": ["mol_016"]}, {"pathway_id": "P4", "name": "Sulfur-rich volcanic spark-discharge rou